Get
	Raspberry Pi 3
	A HDMI display (with HDMI cable)
	A USB keyboard and mouse
	16 GB SD Card
	Power supply cable for Pi

Install Raspbian Stretch on the 16GB SD Card
	https://www.raspberrypi.org/downloads/

sudo raspi-config
	Change Password
		rfid
	Internationalisation/Localisation Options
		Change Timezone
			Asia/Kolkata
		Change Keyboard Layout
			Dell 101 Key PC, Other, English US, English US, The default for the keyboard, No compose key, No
		Wifi Country
			India
	Interfacing Options
		SSH
		SPI
	Advanced Options
		Expand filesystem
	Finish and Reboot

Setup LAN/Wifi
	Wifi - just use the GUI to connect
	LAN in Stretch is different (have to use dhcpcd.conf)
		https://www.raspberrypi.org/forums/viewtopic.php?t=191140 
	Reboot

Test SSH

sudo nano /etc/apt/apt.conf
	Acquire::http::Proxy "http://raghu:backspace@172.16.101.138:3128/";
	Acquire::https::Proxy "http://raghu:backspace@172.16.101.138:3128/";	
sudo apt-get update
sudo nano ~/.bashrc
	#Export Proxy
	export http_proxy=http://raghu:backspace@172.16.101.138:3128/
	export https_proxy=http://raghu:backspace@172.16.101.138:3128/
source ~/.bashrc

Clone https://github.com/krishraghuram/mess-rpisetup
Follow all instructions in "Todo" file
Complete it and Test it before continuing!!!

cd ~
git clone https://github.com/krishraghuram/mess.git
cd mess

sudo apt-get install mariadb-server
sudo apt-get install libmariadbclient-dev
sudo mysql -u root
	CREATE DATABASE mess;
	CREATE USER 'mess'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'mess';
	GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON mess . * TO 'mess'@'localhost';
	FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
sudo -E -H pip install -r requirements.txt

cd ~/mess
python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate
python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:8000